## Ground Truth Generation Methodology

### Overview
Ground truth relevance judgments are generated via a **3-stage pooling + synthetic approach**:

### Stage 1: Synthetic Query Generation (from known-relevant docs)
```rust
/// For each document, generate 1-3 queries it should answer
/// Uses rule-based extraction (not LLM) for reproducibility
pub fn generate_synthetic_queries(doc: &Document) -> Vec<SyntheticQuery> {
    let mut queries = Vec::new();

    // Type 1: Entity queries (extract named entities → "tweets about {entity}")
    for entity in extract_entities(&doc.text) {
        queries.push(SyntheticQuery {
            text: format!("tweets mentioning {}", entity),
            source_doc_id: doc.id.clone(),
            relevance: 2,  // Source doc is always highly relevant
            query_type: QueryType::Entity,
        });
    }

    // Type 2: Temporal queries (extract dates → "what happened on {date}")
    if let Some(date) = doc.created_at {
        queries.push(SyntheticQuery {
            text: format!("messages from {}", date.format("%B %Y")),
            source_doc_id: doc.id.clone(),
            relevance: 2,
            query_type: QueryType::Temporal,
        });
    }

    // Type 3: Topical queries (extract key phrases → "discussions about {topic}")
    for phrase in extract_keyphrases(&doc.text, 3) {
        queries.push(SyntheticQuery {
            text: format!("discussions about {}", phrase),
            source_doc_id: doc.id.clone(),
            relevance: 2,
            query_type: QueryType::Topical,
        });
    }

    queries
}
```

### Stage 2: Candidate Pooling (BM25 + baseline embedder)
```rust
/// For each generated query, find additional potentially-relevant docs
/// using multiple retrieval methods (pooling eliminates single-system bias)
pub fn pool_candidates(
    query: &str,
    corpus: &[Document],
    bm25_index: &BM25Index,
    embedder: &dyn Embedder,  // baseline embedder (e.g., all-MiniLM-L6-v2)
) -> Vec<CandidateDoc> {
    let mut candidates = HashSet::new();

    // Pool from BM25 (lexical matches)
    let bm25_results = bm25_index.search(query, 30);
    for r in &bm25_results {
        candidates.insert(r.doc_id.clone());
    }

    // Pool from embedding similarity (semantic matches)
    let query_vec = embedder.embed(&[query]).unwrap();
    let embed_results = brute_force_topk(&query_vec[0], corpus, 30);
    for r in &embed_results {
        candidates.insert(r.doc_id.clone());
    }

    // Union of both pools = candidate set for judgment
    candidates.into_iter()
        .map(|id| CandidateDoc { doc_id: id })
        .collect()
}
```

### Stage 3: Automated Relevance Grading
```rust
/// Grade candidates using reproducible heuristics (no LLM dependency)
/// Relevance levels: 2=highly relevant, 1=partially relevant, 0=not relevant
pub fn grade_relevance(query: &str, doc: &Document) -> u8 {
    let query_terms: HashSet<&str> = query.split_whitespace()
        .filter(|w| w.len() > 2)
        .collect();
    let doc_terms: HashSet<&str> = doc.text.split_whitespace().collect();

    let overlap = query_terms.intersection(&doc_terms).count();
    let query_coverage = overlap as f64 / query_terms.len().max(1) as f64;

    // Additional signals
    let has_exact_phrase = doc.text.to_lowercase()
        .contains(&query.to_lowercase());
    let entity_match = entities_overlap(query, &doc.text);

    if has_exact_phrase || (query_coverage > 0.8 && entity_match) {
        2  // Highly relevant
    } else if query_coverage > 0.4 || entity_match {
        1  // Partially relevant
    } else {
        0  // Not relevant (excluded from relevants map)
    }
}
```

### Reproducibility Guarantees
- **No LLM in the loop**: All judgments are rule-based (term overlap, entity matching, phrase matching)
- **Deterministic**: Same corpus + same script = identical judgments every run
- **Seed-controlled**: Document sampling uses fixed seed (`CORPUS_SEED=42`)
- **Versioned**: Corpus generation script outputs a `corpus_version` field for tracking

### Query Type Distribution (minimum per type)
| Query Type | Count | Example |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| Entity | >=30 | "tweets mentioning @elonmusk" |
| Temporal | >=25 | "messages from March 2024" |
| Topical | >=40 | "discussions about AI safety" |
| Conversational | >=25 | "DM conversations about project deadlines" |
| Factual | >=30 | "tweets with links to arxiv papers" |

### Difficulty Buckets
```rust
pub enum QueryDifficulty {
    Easy,    // >=5 highly relevant docs, distinctive terms
    Medium,  // 2-4 highly relevant docs, some ambiguity
    Hard,    // 0-1 highly relevant docs, requires semantic understanding
}

/// Assign difficulty based on pool results
pub fn classify_difficulty(query: &str, pool_results: &[PoolResult]) -> QueryDifficulty {
    let highly_relevant = pool_results.iter()
        .filter(|r| r.relevance == 2)
        .count();
    match highly_relevant {
        5.. => QueryDifficulty::Easy,
        2..=4 => QueryDifficulty::Medium,
        _ => QueryDifficulty::Hard,
    }
}
```

Target distribution: ~40% Easy, ~35% Medium, ~25% Hard

