 {"id":"bd-rl9","title":"Task: Implement daemon client with auto-spawn and fallback","description":"## Task: Implement Daemon Client with Auto-Spawn and Fallback

Build the client library that xf uses to communicate with the model daemon.
The client is the primary interface between xf search commands and the warm model daemon.

## Architecture

### Socket Discovery
- Default path: /tmp/xf-daemon-{uid}.sock (or XF_DAEMON_SOCK env override)
- Lock file: /tmp/xf-daemon-{uid}.lock (prevents double-spawn)
- PID file: /tmp/xf-daemon-{uid}.pid (for status/stop commands)

### Auto-Spawn Protocol
```rust
pub struct DaemonClient {
    socket_path: PathBuf,
    connect_timeout: Duration,   // 2s default
    request_timeout: Duration,   // 30s default
    max_retries: u8,             // 3 default
}

impl DaemonClient {
    /// Connect to existing daemon or spawn a new one
    pub async fn connect_or_spawn(config: &DaemonConfig) -> Result<Self> {
        // 1. Try connect to existing socket
        // 2. If ENOENT/ECONNREFUSED: acquire lock file
        // 3. Spawn daemon as background process (fork+exec)
        // 4. Wait for socket to appear (poll with backoff)
        // 5. Connect and send Health check
        // 6. Release lock file
    }
}
```

### Spawn Sequence
1. Check lock file (flock, non-blocking)
2. If locked: another client is spawning, wait for socket
3. Fork daemon process with: nice(10), ionice(idle), setsid()
4. Daemon writes PID file after socket bind succeeds
5. Client polls for socket existence (50ms intervals, max 5s)
6. Client connects and verifies Health response

### Connection Retry Policy
- Exponential backoff: 50ms, 100ms, 200ms (3 retries)
- On all retries exhausted: fall back to direct inference
- Socket EOF during request: single reconnect attempt
- Daemon crash (EPIPE): log warning, fallback immediately

### Fallback to Direct Inference
```rust
pub enum InferenceMode {
    Daemon(DaemonClient),
    Direct(Box<dyn Embedder>), // Falls back to loading model in-process
}

impl InferenceMode {
    /// Transparently handles daemon failure
    pub async fn embed(&self, texts: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>> {
        match self {
            Self::Daemon(client) => {
                match client.send_embed(texts).await {
                    Ok(result) => Ok(result),
                    Err(e) => {
                        tracing::warn!("Daemon failed ({e}), falling back to direct");
                        // Load model in-process, cache for subsequent calls
                        self.upgrade_to_direct().await
                    }
                }
            }
            Self::Direct(embedder) => embedder.embed_batch(texts),
        }
    }
}
```

